news.title: West Bengal government to soon auction several land parcels in Alipore
news.para: The Housing Infrastructure Development Corporation (Hidco) has fixed a starting bid price of Rs 236.7 crore for a 5.6 acre plot at the rate of Rs 42.3 crore per acre.

news.title: Maharashtra government approves ULPIN for land parcels, rollout next month
news.para: Confirming the development, state settlement commissioner N K Sudhanshu told TOI that a GR (government resolution) had been issued on the Unique Land Parcel Identification Number (ULPIN).

news.title: Land sold after undertaking development activities should attract 18% GST: Madhya Pradesh AAAR
news.para: Any land sold after undertaking development activities such as providing water line, electricity or sanitation facility should attract 18% GST, Madhya Pradesh AAAR ruled.

news.title: Noida: Supertech hires firm to repair Emerald Court basements
news.para: With just four weeks to go for the demolition of the twin towers on August 21, a contractor has been belatedly appointed to fix the basements of other buildings of Emerald Court.

news.title: Gurugram: Panel to conduct structural audit of 60 high-rises yet to be constituted
news.para: DTCP had shortlisted five highrise societies — Raheja Vedanta in Sector 108, Raheja Atharva in Sector 109, Brisk Lumbini in Sector 109, M3M Woodshire in Sector 107 and Mahindra Aura in Sector 110A — for a structural audit by IIT-Roorkee.

news.title: Pardos Real Estate acquires seven-acre land in Gurgaon for Rs 180 crore
news.para: The company is expected to construct an office tower on the acquired land, the people cited earlier said, adding that CBRE India has facilitated the deal.

news.title: ABIL group chairman diverted Rs 300 crore of DHFL money for buying property in London: CBI
news.para: ​​The central agency has arrested Bhosale in an alleged scam involving Dewan Housing Finance Ltd (DHFL) and Yes Bank. The charge sheet was filed before a special CBI court here earlier this week.

news.title: Orient Cement's net profit declines 58% to Rs 37 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Its revenue from operation was up 3.33 per cent to Rs 713.93 crore during the quarter under review. It was Rs 690.90 crore in the corresponding period of last fiscal.

news.title: Abu Dhabi's Aldar Properties posts 54% jump in profit in Apr-June 2022
news.para: Profit attributable to shareholders came in at 803.99 million dirhams ($218.91 million) for the three months to June 30, compared with 520.83 million dirhams a year earlier.

news.title: Sundaram Home Finance posts net profit of Rs 47.26 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Disbursements during the quarter under review grew to Rs 796 crore from Rs 249 crore registered same quarter previous year, a company statement said here.

news.title: China Evergrande gets bid from CK Asset for Hong Kong headquarters building
news.para: With more than $300 billion in liabilities, Evergrande has been trying to sell its 26-storey China Evergrande Centre in Hong Kong's Wan Chai district after a potential $1.7 billion deal collapsed late last year, as part of the asset disposal effort to raise fund.

news.title: China targets $148 billion in financing for cash-strapped developers
news.para: The People's Bank of China (PBOC) will initially issue about 200 billion yuan of low-interest loans, charging about 1.75% a year, to state commercial banks, the FT said, citing people involved in the discussions.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance net profit dips 3.4% to Rs 235 crore in April-June
news.para: Revenues in the first quarter of FY23 were down at Rs 1,412 crore as against Rs 1,693 crore in the year-ago period, PNB Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Asia's richest woman loses half her wealth in China property crisis
news.para: Yang Huiyan, a majority shareholder in Chinese property giant Country Garden, saw her net worth plunge by more than 52 percent to $11.3 billion from $23.7 billion a year ago, according to the Bloomberg Billionaires Index.

news.title: Shree Cement's net profit falls 55.8% to Rs 278.86 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: However, its revenue from operations increased 21.45 per cent to Rs 4,414.85 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 3,634.83 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding fiscal.
